        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="584" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d584">
                <head>Municipal Council of Scarborough</head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Scarborough</placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-08">May 8, 1865</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="italic">Resolution passed at a meeting of the council of the
                            borough of Scarborough, in the county of York, held in the Town Hall, on
                            Monday, May</hi> 8, 1865.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Resolved unanimously</hi>, That this council desires to
                        express its feelings of horror and indignation at the assassination of the
                        President of the United States, and the barbarous attempt on the lives of
                        Secretary Seward and his son; and also its deep sympathy with the people of
                        the United States, as well as with the widow and family of the President, at
                        the great loss they have sustained.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Signed on behalf of the council:</salute>
                    <signed>AMBROSE GIBSON, </signed>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mayor</hi>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
